http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Inmates%E2%80%99-patriotic-moves/article14022162.ece

Their energy was palpable as they danced to Maa Tujhe Salam and Baarisu Kannada Dindimava . This was the first public performance of 16 inmates lodged in the district central prison in Vijayapura.“The opportunity was given to us by the jail authorities, who arranged for an instructor,” said an excited Santosh Kempashetty, one of the performers. Many inmates said if such events were held routinely, it would help reform themselves.Choreographer Anees Hussain Ingleshwar said that he never thought the inmates would learn so quickly. “I gave them only six days of training and they grasped the steps quickly,” he said.